{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The conversation history passed to the LLM is trimmed to the most recent 10 messages when the full history exceeds the context window.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"A unit test of only the trimming helper can pass even if orchestration forgets to apply trimming before the LLM call (MOCK-MISS). The real failure boundary is module wiring: history builder + request composer + LLM client interface.","test_description":"Wire the chatbot service with a fake in-process LLM client that records request payloads. Provide 15-message history, execute response generation, and assert the payload sent to the LLM contains exactly the most recent 10 messages in correct order.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.25,"Integration":0.65,"System":0.06,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"The generated response addresses the customer's question rather than producing a generic or off-topic reply.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"This is a response-quality claim that depends on real LLM behavior (LLM-DEP). Mocked outputs would hide failures in relevance, and repeated real runs can vary.","test_description":"Run against the production/staging LLM for a fixed set of customer questions with gold relevance criteria. Score outputs with human-labeled rubric or an agreed evaluator and fail if relevance rate drops below threshold (e.g., >=90% on set).","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.04,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.82,"Workflow":0.08}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The tone re-check correctly identifies when a response is too formal for a casual-tier customer and triggers regeneration.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Correct tone identification is model-judgment dependent (LLM-DEP). Integration tests can verify trigger wiring but cannot validate real misclassification risk if checker is mocked (MOCK-HIDE).","test_description":"Use real tone-check model/prompt on a curated set of overly formal responses labeled for casual tier. Assert high detection recall, and in the same test assert the orchestrator performs a regeneration call whenever flagged.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.03,"Integration":0.2,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.62,"Workflow":0.1}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"The full exchange (user message, generated response, any regenerations) is persisted to the database with correct timestamps.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Persistence bugs often appear only with real DB schema/transactions/timestamp handling; pure mocks can miss them (MOCK-MISS). No external network/process is required if using local test DB.","test_description":"Run chatbot flow with a local test database. Trigger one normal reply and one tone-regenerated reply, then query stored records and assert all turns (including rejected draft + final) are present with correct linkage and non-null, correctly ordered timestamps.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.1,"Integration":0.78,"System":0.09,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"When the tone check triggers regeneration, the second response replaces the first — the customer never sees the rejected draft.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure boundary is orchestration between generation, tone-check decision, and outward response object. Unit tests of individual functions can miss leaked first-draft wiring bugs (MOCK-MISS).","test_description":"Use deterministic stubs for generation (first='formal draft', second='casual rewrite') and tone-check (flag first only). Execute end-to-end service call in-process and assert returned/streamed customer-visible response equals second draft only, while first draft is only internal/logged.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.08,"Integration":0.74,"System":0.12,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.03}}]}
